Introduction

Croatia is a Central European and Mediterranean nation that shares lengthy maritime borders with Italy in the Adriatic Sea and borders Slovenia to the west, Hungary to the north, Serbia to the east, and Bosnia and Herzegovina to the south. Together, these borders measure 2,028 km.

Croatia is unlike any other country in the world and has a peculiar shape (like a croissant!). The Ottoman (Turkish) empires five centuries of expansion into Central Europe are what gave it this peculiar shape. (However, despite this, the Turks never fully took control of Croatia; they did, however, rule over parts of its neighbors, including Serbia and Bosnia and Hercegovina.) On our history of Croatia page, we have more information about Croatias past if that interests you.

With a land area of 56,691 square kilometers and a population of 3.88 million, Croatia is a large country (2021 census quite a fall from 4.29 million people recorded in the 2011 census). There are minorities of Serbian, Bosnian, Hungarian, and Italian in addition to the almost 90% Croat (most of whom are Roman Catholic) majority.

Discussion

1143354 confirmed cases of COVID-19 and 16043 fatalities have been reported as a result of the COVID-19 pandemic in Croatia.

On February 25, a patient from Italy who had traveled to Zagreb was found to have the disease after testing positive. This was the country of Croatias first case. The second instance connected to the first one was confirmed on the same day. A number of incidents were recorded in different Croatian cities in March 2020. The first recovery was recorded on March 12 and the first confirmed virus-related death was discovered on March 18. .During Croatias time in office as EU Council president, a pandemic struck the country. The Croatian capital of Zagreb was struck by the largest earthquake in 140 years on March 22, 2020, which made it difficult to carry out the governments plans for social segregation during the countrys lockdown in the latter portion of the first half of 2020. A national election for parliament was conducted on July 5, 2020. Local elections were held nationwide on May 16, 2021. During the summer of 2020, when tourists were most in demand, the nation was largely reopened.
